<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>In the <span class="Emphasis">Description</span> field, enter content and format it using the rich text editor options.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Select existing description text where you want to add a link.</p>
                <p>
                    <img src="../../../Images/Central/Tasks/Tasks-Rich-Text-Editor-Link2.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth100Percent" />
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Click <img src="../../../Images/Central/Tasks/Tasks-Rich-Text-Editor-Link-btn.png" alt="" title="" class="ReduceButtonSize" />.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>From the context menu, verify the text, and add a hyperlink for the text. (The Text and Link fields can include the same information.)</p>
                <p>
                    <img src="../../../Images/Central/Tasks/Tasks-Rich-Text-Editor-Link3.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth100Percent" />
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Click <span class="Emphasis">Apply</span>.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Notice the link is active in the description. Click <span class="Emphasis">Save</span>.</p>
                <p>
                    <img src="../../../Images/Central/Tasks/Tasks-Rich-Text-Editor-Link4.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth100Percent" />
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </body>
</html>